Example 3.1.1 from Experimental Design & Analysis for Tree Improvement

Source: R/Exam3.1.1.R
Exam3.1.1.Rd

Exam3.1.1 is part of data from Australian Centre for Agricultural Research (ACIAR) in Queensland, Australia (Experiment 309).

References

  1. Williams, E.R., Matheson, A.C. and Harwood, C.E. (2002).Experimental Design and Analysis for Tree Improvement. CSIRO Publishing.

See also

DataExam3.1.1

Examples


library(tidyverse)
data(DataExam3.1.1)

fm3.8   <-     lm(
   formula     = Mean~Repl+SeedLot
 , data        = DataExam3.1.1
 #, subset
 #, weights
 #, na.action
 , method      = "qr"
 , model       = TRUE
 , x           = FALSE
 , y           = FALSE
 , qr          = TRUE
 , singular.ok = TRUE
 , contrasts   = NULL
  )
anova(fm3.8)
#> Analysis of Variance Table
#> 
#> Response: Mean
#>           Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)   
#> Repl       1  2.538  2.5376  3.4197 0.138108   
#> SeedLot    4 63.234 15.8084 21.3035 0.005851 **
#> Residuals  4  2.968  0.7421                    
#> ---
#> Signif. codes:  0 ‘***’ 0.001 ‘**’ 0.01 ‘*’ 0.05 ‘.’ 0.1 ‘ ’ 1
DataExam3.1.1 %>%
dplyr::ungroup() %>%
 dplyr::group_by(SeedLot) %>%
 dplyr::summarize(Mean=mean(Mean))
#> `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
#> # A tibble: 5 x 2
#>   SeedLot       Mean
#>   <fct>        <dbl>
#> 1 Acacia       10.3 
#> 2 Angophora     7.1 
#> 3 Casuarina     5.51
#> 4 Melaleuca     4.94
#> 5 Petalostigma  2.73
